                        <button class="tab-btn tab-btn-builder active" id="tabBuilder" onclick="toggleAbout('builder')"
                            aria-pressed="true">
                            <span class="tab-btn-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                                <!-- Wrench / builder icon -->
                                <svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor"
                                    stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                                    <path
                                        d="M14.7 6.3a1 1 0 0 0 0 1.4l1.6 1.6a1 1 0 0 0 1.4 0l3.77-3.77a6 6 0 0 1-7.94 7.94l-6.91 6.91a2.12 2.12 0 0 1-3-3l6.91-6.91a6 6 0 0 1 7.94-7.94l-3.76 3.76z" />
                                </svg>
                            </span>
                            <span class="tab-btn-label">The Builder</span>
                        </button>

                        <button class="tab-btn tab-btn-human" id="tabHuman" onclick="toggleAbout('human')"
                            aria-pressed="false">
                            <span class="tab-btn-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                                <!-- Coffee cup / human icon -->
                                <svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor"
                                    stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                                    <path d="M17 8h1a4 4 0 1 1 0 8h-1" />
                                    <path d="M3 8h14v9a4 4 0 0 1-4 4H7a4 4 0 0 1-4-4Z" />
                                    <line x1="6" y1="2" x2="6" y2="4" />
                                    <line x1="10" y1="2" x2="10" y2="4" />
                                    <line x1="14" y1="2" x2="14" y2="4" />
                                </svg>
                            </span>
                            <span class="tab-btn-label">The Human</span>
                        </button>
                    </div>

                    <!-- The Builder Content -->
                    <div id="bio-builder" class="about-content active-bio">
                        <p class="about-text">
                            I’m a third-year Electronics and Instrumentation Engineering student at MIT, Anna
                            University.
                            Over the past two years, my curiosity about how complex systems work has evolved into a
                            hands-on
                            obsession with building them. I don't just want to understand the theory; I want to wire it,
                            code it, and make it run.
                        </p>
                        <br>
                        <p class="about-text">
                            From designing digital logic in Vivado and soldering IoT prototypes at hackathons to
                            training
                            predictive AI for functional safety, I love operating right where hardware meets software.
                            My
                            philosophy is simple: <strong>I build to learn, and I simulate to build better.</strong>
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <!-- The Human Content -->
                    <div id="bio-human" class="about-content hidden-bio">
                        <p class="about-text">
                            When I’m not buried in hardware data sheets or debugging code, you can usually find me
                            touching grass—literally and figuratively—with my hackathon crew,
                            <strong>TouchGrass.Devs</strong>. We thrive on the chaos of 24-hour sprints, whether we're
                            debugging web interfaces under pressure or racing against the clock to hunt down IoT
                            components.
                        </p>
                        <br>
                        <p class="about-text">
                            Off the clock, I'm a massive film freak. I treat my Letterboxd diary like a second
                            portfolio, tracking, rating, and overanalyzing cinematography. To unwind, I usually step
                            away from the screens entirely to play the musical keyboard, or log onto Chess.com for a
                            quick mental reset. I'm fueled by great storytelling, collaborative chaos, and a good
                            Spotify playlist.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                </div>
            </section>


